<paragraph id="16F8042DB43D9E585DF1CDA19AEE6398" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis id="339CA871DF29F9EE9D3DD264F8E79528" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="03A3E72D2209C9F723919A50A29966EE" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hastigera">
<emphasis id="3191F225F18D3E9E681C054B0CEF9A7A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">I. hastigera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the sagittate or hastate leaves, extended inflorescence with secondary peduncles 2-12 mm long, outer sepals 5-6 
<normalizedToken id="BDF7C074322BE53163E7725A055DB197" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
3-5 mm, the corolla tube 2.7-3 cm, the limb deeply lobed, 2.5-3 cm diam. Capsules at least sometimes with a persistent style.
</paragraph>
